Frances Moore Lappé's Lentils, Monastery Style
https://food52.com/recipes/35254-frances-moore-lappe-s-lentils-monastery-style

1/4 cup olive oil
2 large onions, chopped
1 carrot, chopped
1/2 teaspoon dried thyme
1/2 teaspoon dried marjoram
3 cups stock
1 cup lentils, rinsed
1 pinch Salt, to taste
1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley
1 16 ounce can tomatoes
1/4 cup dry sherry
2/3 cup grated Swiss cheese

Heat oil in a large pot and sauté the onions and carrot for 3 to 5 minutes,
until softened and onion is translucent. Add dried herbs and sauté 1 minute.
Add stock, lentils, salt, parsley, and tomatoes and cook, covered, until
lentils are tender, about 45 minutes. Add sherry.

To serve, put 2 tablespoons cheese in each bowl and fill with soup.
